      • put

        public void put(GraphSerialisable graph,
                FederatedAccess access)
         throws StorageException
        places a graph into storage, protected by the given access.

        GraphId can't already exist, otherwise OverwritingException is thrown.

        Access can't be null otherwise IllegalArgumentException is thrown

        Parameters:
        graph - the graph to add to the storage.
        access - access required to for the graph.
        Throws:
        StorageException - if unable to put arguments into storage
